high_load.body:
Dear {client_name} Team,

High system load has been detected on one of your servers.

Details:
  Host       : {host_name}
  IP Address : {host_ip}
  AWS Account: {aws_account}
  Load Avg   : {alert_value}
  Time       : {timestamp}

Recommended Actions:
  1. Check running processes and identify any stuck or high-CPU tasks
  2. Review recent deployments or scheduled jobs that may have triggered the load
  3. If load remains high, consider horizontal scaling or restarting services

Our team is monitoring the situation.

Regards,
AeonX Cloud Operations Team
+91-XXXXXXXXXX | support@aeonx.digital

host_restarted.body:
Dear {client_name} Team,

This is an informational notification that your server has been restarted.

Details:
  Host       : {host_name}
  IP Address : {host_ip}
  AWS Account: {aws_account}
  Time       : {timestamp}

The server is back online and operating normally. No action is required from your side.

If this restart was unexpected, please review your system logs for the cause.
For any concerns, contact us at support@aeonx.digital

Regards,
AeonX Cloud Operations Team
+91-XXXXXXXXXX | support@aeonx.digital

ec2_terminated.body:
Dear {client_name} Team,

Urgent: An EC2 instance in your environment has been terminated.

Details:
  Host       : {host_name}
  IP Address : {host_ip}
  AWS Account: {aws_account}
  Time       : {timestamp}

This is a critical event. A terminated EC2 instance cannot be restarted — a new instance must be launched.

Our team has been alerted and is investigating immediately.
Expect an update within 15 minutes.

For urgent assistance: contact@aeonx.digital or call +91-XXXXXXXXXX

Regards,
AeonX Cloud Operations Team

